<item>
            <title>[SPARK-48802] FileStreamSource: maxCachedFiles set to 0 causes empty batches</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-48802</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While testing changes from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-44924&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-44924&lt;/a&gt; it was discovered that setting &lt;tt&gt;maxCachedFiles&lt;/tt&gt; to 0 to try to force each batch to perform a full listing was inadvertently causing every other batch to trigger with no files being processed.&#160; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case, the list of &lt;tt&gt;unselectedFiles&lt;/tt&gt; from a file listing gets 0 files taken from it and assigned to &lt;tt&gt;unreadFiles&lt;/tt&gt; as an empty list, which is re-used in the next batch and only checked if &lt;tt&gt;unreadFiles&lt;/tt&gt; is null.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Tested with Spark 4.0 RC&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
